In the movie &quot;Contact,&quot; Matthew McConaughey&#x27;s character, Palmer Joss, says to Ellie Arroway, played by Jodie Foster:

&quot;Did you love your father? [...] Prove it.&quot; 

This line is part of a larger conversation about faith and belief, where Palmer is challenging Ellie on her demand for empirical evidence of everything, suggesting that some of the most profound truths cannot be proven scientifically.

